<item>
            <title>[HBASE-6103] Optimize the HBaseServer to deserialize the data for each ipc connection in parallel</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-6103</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently HBaseServer is running with a single listener thread, which is responsible for accepting the connection, reading the data from network channel, deserializing the data into writable objects and handover to the IPC handler threads. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When there are multiple hbase clients connecting to the region server (HBaseServer) and reading/writing a large set of data, the listener and the respond thread will be performance bottleneck. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So the solution is to deserialize the data for each ipc connection in parallel for HBaseServer&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;BTW, it is also one of the reasons that the parallel scanning from multiple clients is far slower than single client case.&lt;/p&gt;






</description>
